  "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/corpus/quantum-computing",
  "@type": "Corpus",
  "titulo": "Corpus de artigos científicos sobre Computação Quântica",
  "descricao": "Ontologia JSON-LD gerada a partir das etapas de pré-processamento, extração de informações e análise de frequência de termos.",
  "temArtigo": [
    {
      "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf",
      "@type": [
        "ArtigoCientifico",
        "schema:ScholarlyArticle"
      ],
      "arquivo": "1-s2.0-S266630742500035X-main.pdf",
      "titulo": "Integrating artificial intelligence and quantum computing: A systematic",
      "temObjetivo": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/objetivo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "Consequently, this study aims to identify the applications and variables associated with QC-AI integration."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/objetivo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "This study aims to systematically examine the intersection of quantum computing and artificial intelligence by identifying the key technological features, integration requirements, and sectoral applications that define the current state of the field."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/objetivo/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "This study aims to identify QC applications and methodologies applied to AI and to assess their impact on process optimization and complex problem-solving."
        }
      ],
      "temProblema": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/problema/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "Despite significant progress, AI-QC integration faces critical limitations: dependence on NISQ hardware with high error rates, lack of standardized methodologies, and insufficient conceptual frameworks for articulating applications and technical requirements (Ghodke et al., 2024)."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/problema/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "However, these advantages are problem-specific and have been rigorously proven only for certain algorithms, such as Shor’s and Grover’s (Moret-Bonillo, 2015)."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/problema/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "However, the lack of structured knowledge regarding specific QC methodologies and applications in AI hinders its optimal implementation and development."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/problema/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "The study concludes that although QC demonstrates substantial potential to enhance AI, its broader adoption remains constrained by reliance on NISQ hardware, the need for effective error correction, and the limited scalability of hybrid quantum classical algorithms."
        }
      ],
      "temMetodologia": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/metodo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "To this end, a systematic literature review was conducted following the PRISMA 2020 methodology, drawing on studies from Scopus and Web of Science databases."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/metodo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "According to PRISMA 2020 is employed to identify and analyze applications and methodologies at the intersection of QC and AI, an interdisciplinary field that demands rigorous approaches to integrate high-quality and relevant studies."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/metodo/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "Healthcare; spectroscopy and imaging (NMR, MRI, control of spin) Quantum control, evolutionary algorithms, RF pulse optimization, design of experiments, inhomogeneity compensation Subrahmanian et al. (2022) Hybrid Entanglement Distribution between Remote Microwave Quantum Computers Empowered by Machine Learning USA (University of Arizona, USC) Theoretical proposal and simulation; development of a hybrid CVDV protocol for entanglement distribution with ML optimization Quantum computer connectivity (microwave QC) Entanglement distribution, hybrid CVDV protocol, microwave-optical transduction, ML optimization, superconductor integration Zhang et al."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/metodo/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "Machine Learning for Electronic Structure Calculations of Periodic Systems on Quantum Computing Devices USA Hybrid quantumclassical approach using restricted Boltzmann machines and IBM-Q simulations to calculate the electronic structure of periodic systems Materials science; computational chemistry (calculation of electronic structures) Hybrid quantumclassical algorithms, ML potentials, electronic calculations, quantum device benchmarking Sureshbabu et al."
        }
      ],
      "temContribuicao": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/contribuicao/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "contribuicao",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "The review contributes by mapping existing research, highlighting methodological approaches, and revealing gaps that may guide targeted advancements in hybrid quantum AI systems."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/contribuicao/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "contribuicao",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "These contributions aim to guide future experimental validations and hybrid model development."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/contribuicao/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "contribuicao",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "The insights generated have the potential to accelerate innovation in high-impact domains such as healthcare, finance, energy, and cybersecurity."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/contribuicao/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "contribuicao",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "Additionally, this review introduces an integrative framework that categorizes key AI QC convergence dimensions and proposes a classification of application areas based on technical requirements and algorithmic capabilities."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/1-s2-0-s266630742500035x-main-pdf/contribuicao/5",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "contribuicao",
          "ordem": 5,
          "texto": "The contributions are threefold: (i) providing a structured synthesis and classification of literature on QC-AI inte gration under NISQ constraints, (ii) presenting sector-based examples that illustrate opportunities and use cases, and (iii) outlining a forwardlooking research agenda to guide the use of QC in enhancing AI."
        }
      ],
