    {
      "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10115-026-02685-6-pdf",
      "@type": [
        "ArtigoCientifico",
        "schema:ScholarlyArticle"
      ],
      "arquivo": "s10115-026-02685-6.pdf",
      "titulo": "Knowledge and Information Systems (2026) 68:84",
      "temObjetivo": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10115-026-02685-6-pdf/objetivo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "To bridge this gap, this paper proposes a quantum recurrent neural network (QRNN) designed specifically for sequential labeling tasks."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10115-026-02685-6-pdf/objetivo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "To overcome this research gap, we propose a hybrid quantum-classical recurrent neural network (QRNN) that is used specifically for sequential labeling tasks."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10115-026-02685-6-pdf/objetivo/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "The proposed QRNN is a hybrid quantum-classical model, which combines quantum and classical resources."
        }
      ],
      "temProblema": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10115-026-02685-6-pdf/problema/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "However, the superiority of transformer-based models poses various challenges, such as demands for a large amount of data and parameters to train models [4]."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10115-026-02685-6-pdf/problema/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "Quantum computing can efficiently solve problems that are difficult for traditional computing, such as factoring large numbers [7]."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10115-026-02685-6-pdf/problema/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "Although several studies have explored the application of QML techniques to NLP such as language modeling [17], text classification [18], and sentiment analysis [19], there is still a noticeable research gap in applying quantum-enhanced architectures to sequential labeling, a core problem in NLP that involves assigning categorical labels to each token in a sequence."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10115-026-02685-6-pdf/problema/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "However, these algorithms cannot be applied to current quantum hardware due to their dependence on quantum RAM to execute."
        }
      ],
      "temMetodologia": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10115-026-02685-6-pdf/metodo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "All the experiments are implemented on Penny Lane framework on its local simulator default-qubit except the noise model, which is performed on default.mixed simulator."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10115-026-02685-6-pdf/metodo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "In our experiments, stochastic gradient optimization is used to optimize the VQC parameters and weight matrix W."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10115-026-02685-6-pdf/metodo/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "However, the proposed model utilizes angle encoding, which is an efficient data encoding method for QNNs."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10115-026-02685-6-pdf/metodo/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "QRNN is applied to perform POS tagging in nine different code-mixed datasets, where each dataset represents a unique combination of languages."
        }
      ],
      "temContribuicao": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10115-026-02685-6-pdf/contribuicao/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "contribuicao",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "Our main contribution is: 1. to develop a QRNN that combines VQCs with classical layers to perform efficient sequential labeling; 2. to evaluate QRNN performance employing part-of-speech (POS) tagging, a sequence labeling task on nine different code-mixed datasets, and 3. to present ablation studies that examine the influence of different data encoding methods, entanglement strategies, and variational circuit depths on model performance."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10115-026-02685-6-pdf/contribuicao/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "contribuicao",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "This novel model shows the potential of QRNN for efficiently labeling input sequences."
        }
      ],
