        "48. Bergholm V , Izaac J, Schuld M, Gogolin C, Ahmed S, Ajith V , Alam MS, Alonso-Linaje G, Akash Narayanan B, Asadi A, et al (2018) Pennylane: Automatic differentiation of hybrid quantum-classical computations. ar Xiv preprint ar Xiv:1811.04968 Publisher’s Note Springer Nature remains neutral with regard to jurisdictional claims in published maps and institutional afﬁliations. Springer Nature or its licensor (e.g. a society or other partner) holds exclusive rights to this article under a publishing agreement with the author(s) or other rightsholder(s); author self-archiving of the accepted manuscript version of this article is solely governed by the terms of such publishing agreement and applicable law. 123 Quantum recurrent neural network for sequential labeling Page 23 of 23    84 Shyambabu Pandey is a Ph.D. Scholar in the Department of Computer Science and Engineering at the National Institute of Technology Silchar, India. His research focuses on quantum computing, quantum machine learning, and natural language processing. He is particularly interested in developing quantum machine learning models for natural language processing applications. Partha Pakray is an Associate Professor in the Department of Computer Science & Engineering at the National Institute of Technology Silchar. He worked as a Postdoctoral Fellow in the Natural Language Processing (NLP) domain at Masaryk University, Czech Republic. He was also a Postdoctoral Fellow at the Norwegian University of Science and Technology from 2013 to 2014. He worked as a Senior Research Engineer at Jadavpur University on the “Development of Cross-Lingual Information Access (CLIA) Phase II” project under the Ministry of Communications & Information Technology, Government of India (2007-2013). His international collaborations include the CONACYT-DST India project titled “Answer V alidation through Textual Entailment” with Alexander Gelbukh from the National Polytechnic Institute, Mexico, and Professor Sivaji Bandyopadhyay from Jadavpur University, India. He visited Mexico in 2011 and 2013 for this project. In 2012, Partha Pakray completed a six-month research internship at Xerox Research Centre Europe (XRCE) in Grenoble, France. He got the workshop project funding on “Quantum Machine Learning for Natural Language Processing Applications” from Meit Y Quantum Computing Applications Lab (QCAL). His research expertise focuses on quantum machine learning for natural language processing application. He has published more than 150 papers in reputed journals, conferences and workshops proceedings, and 5 patents. He received 8 research funded projects from various Government of India funding agencies like DST, SERB, CEFIPRA, DAAD, ASEAN, and Meit Y Quantum Computing Applications Lab (QCAL). He is very active in several international conferences organized by local and international associations, institutions, or universities and is also an editorial board member of Natural Language Engineering (Cambridge Press) journal. Fabio Massimo Zanzotto is an Italian researcher in artiﬁcial intelligence, active in NLP and machine learning since 1998. He has served as an Associate Professor in the Department of Enterprise Engineering at the University of Rome “Tor V ergata” since 2006. His research centers on four main areas: actionable explainability for machine learning models (including NLP and medical applications), Ethics & AI (including a manifesto advocating “fair AI” that repays the knowledge it uses), AI for precision medicine, and recognizing textual entailment (including a book and multiple papers). He has led and contributed to several funded research initiatives, including roles in projects such as SMARTBENCH, SFId A Now, REVERT (H2020), and as Principal Investigator for KA TY (Horizon 2020), STEP , and Class-t AIs (PRIN-2022). His work has also been featured in national media and cultural press outlets (e.g., RAI Scuola and major Italian newspapers). 123"
      ]
    },
    {
      "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10791-026-09990-2-pdf",
      "@type": [
        "ArtigoCientifico",
        "schema:ScholarlyArticle"
      ],
      "arquivo": "s10791-026-09990-2.pdf",
      "titulo": "RESEARCH Open Access",
      "temObjetivo": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10791-026-09990-2-pdf/objetivo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "To address these challenges, a blockchain framework based on a semiquantum key distribution network, referred to as Semi-Quantum Blockchain (SQB), is proposed."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10791-026-09990-2-pdf/objetivo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "In this paper, we propose a Semi-Quantum Blockchain (SQB) scheme that utilizes one-direction quantum walk on a circle. 1."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10791-026-09990-2-pdf/objetivo/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "In SQB, we propose a Po A consensus mechanism that utilizes one-direction quantum walk on a circular topology."
        }
      ],
      "temProblema": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10791-026-09990-2-pdf/problema/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "Quantum attacks represent a significant challenge for blockchain technology. quantum computing disrupts the traditional classical computing paradigm, enabling the rapid resolution of problems that classical computing struggles to address."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10791-026-09990-2-pdf/problema/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "Post-quantum cryptography, however, is based on mathematical computational complexity, with its security rely ing on the difficulty of solving mathematical problems."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10791-026-09990-2-pdf/problema/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "However, with the proliferation of blockchain applications, several technical and security challenges have emerged, including issues related to transaction speed, scalability, and vulnerabilities in smart contracts [1]."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10791-026-09990-2-pdf/problema/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "SQB is the first comprehensive semi-quantum blockchain framework, bridging the gap between resource-intensive quantum blockchains and computationally costly postquantum alternatives."
        }
      ],
      "temMetodologia": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10791-026-09990-2-pdf/metodo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "In the mea surement process, compared with other quantum schemes using QSCD ff problem differentiation algorithm, quantum state comparison techniques and other measure ment methods, this paper’s scheme uses measurement techniques such as single-par ticle measurements and Bell measurements, which are simpler to realize."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10791-026-09990-2-pdf/metodo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "SQB employs an enhanced Po A consensus algorithm, maintaining quantum channels only between authority nodes (including the leader node)."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10791-026-09990-2-pdf/metodo/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "Finally, the hash value h M is computed by jointly processing hp and Mh."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10791-026-09990-2-pdf/metodo/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "The leader node election process is conducted through a quantum voting scheme, which is also based on one-direction quantum walk on a circle [20]."
        }
      ],
      "temContribuicao": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s10791-026-09990-2-pdf/contribuicao/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "contribuicao",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "The security analysis demonstrates that SQB provides robust post-quantum security and significantly outperforms its peers in terms of quantum resource consumption and quantum communication efficiency, establishing it as a secure and efficient blockchain solution."
        }
      ],
