    {
      "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00463-5-pdf",
      "@type": [
        "ArtigoCientifico",
        "schema:ScholarlyArticle"
      ],
      "arquivo": "s40507-026-00463-5.pdf",
      "titulo": "Bharathi et al. EPJ Quantum Technology (2026) 13:20",
      "temObjetivo": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00463-5-pdf/objetivo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "This work introduces Hybrid Quantum Neural Network (HQNN) contrived for overcoming these challenges and facilitate efficient Quantum enabled machine learning for real time intrusion detection systems."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00463-5-pdf/objetivo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "Experimental analysis validates the efficiency of the proposed work compared to existing models, showcasing promising results in Io T environments."
        }
      ],
      "temProblema": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00463-5-pdf/problema/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "In addition, security becomes a difficult problem when Io T devices communicate over wireless channels."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00463-5-pdf/problema/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "All Io T adoption, however, is thought to be particularly sensitive to security and privacy concerns."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00463-5-pdf/problema/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "An effective way to reduce and respond to these cyber threats is to employ network intrusion detection system (IDS)."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00463-5-pdf/problema/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "This system detect and identify vulnerabilities in Io T based systems that pose a major threat to the security of any system connected to it as well as the overall smart environment [1]."
        }
      ],
      "temMetodologia": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00463-5-pdf/metodo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "First, the methodology was validated through quantum simulation, and then the experiments were deployed on an IBM quantum processor to assess real-device performance."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00463-5-pdf/metodo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "The dataset was generated using the Cooja network simulator in the Contiki-NG environment, ensuring accurate emulation of constrained Io T devices and routing behavior."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00463-5-pdf/metodo/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "In our experimentation, the repetition codes are implemented for each dataset (Bo T, ACI and KDD) after encoding features using ZZFeature mapping."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00463-5-pdf/metodo/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "Then final circuit ⨂︂ ⨂︁ Uϕ(x) H ⨂︂ ⨂︁ n H n Uϕ(x) Finally, the information regarding the quantum kernel is extracted from the quantum circuit in order to input it into the quantum SVM algorithm."
        }
      ],
