      "temObjetivo": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00513-y-pdf/objetivo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "In Sect.3 we present results for the distribution cost of several classes ofquantumcircuitsincluding circuits fromthe widely used QASMBench1.4benchmarkingsuite[25].Thiscomparisonestablishestheimportanceof efficient circuit reordering strategies for distributed quantum compiling."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00513-y-pdf/objetivo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "We develop such a strategy in thefollowingsection. 2.2 Agreedyheuristicalgorithmforgatereorderingandpacking Notethattwoadjacentpackets 𝒫i and𝒫i+1 canbemergedintoasinglepacket 𝒬j =𝒫i ·𝒫i+1 if they are rooted on the same control qubit."
        }
      ],
      "temProblema": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00513-y-pdf/problema/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "However, solving real-size problems and relevant industrial use cases requires quantum processing units (QPUs) with a large number of error corrected qubits [1-5]."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00513-y-pdf/problema/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "This remains a core challenge for hardware engineers [6,7], while quantum algorithm researchers are developing methodsallowinglargescalequantumcomputationwithlimitedresources[8]."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00513-y-pdf/problema/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "However, such method is constrained to the gate set (H, Mengonietal."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00513-y-pdf/problema/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "The novel preprocessing strategy employed inthisworkreordersthegatesofaninputcircuit, optimizingtheirgroupingintogatepackets.Theproposedmethodexploitsunitaryoperatorcommutationandcontrol-symmetry oflogicaloperations, aswellasgate-packetmerging, increasingthesizeofgatepacketsand thereby reducing the quantum communication overhead required for non-local operations.Theaboveapproachisshowntobeeffectivelyleveragedfordistributedhypergraphbasedquantumcompilation."
        }
      ],
      "temMetodologia": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00513-y-pdf/metodo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "Non-local operations are implemented using the Tele Gate quantum communication protocol, which consumes one pre-shared EPRpairforeachexecution(see Appendix A)."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00513-y-pdf/metodo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "Under this perspective, the fact that our method performs comparably across several benchmarkinstancesindicatesthatthepreprocessingstagebasedongatereorderingcan alreadyyieldmeaningfulreductionsindistributioncost.Thishelpsclarifythespecificeffectofgatereordering, independentlyoffurtherrefinements.Atthesametime, thetechniques explored in the above works are best viewed as complementary to our approach, andtheirintegrationwiththepresentpreproc essingstageisanaturaldirectionforfuture work. 4C o n c l u s i o n In this work, we presented a greedy heuristic algorithm for efficiently reordering gates duringpreprocessing, alongwiththepackingandpartitioningapproachesintegratedinto ara Qne, thedistributed quantumcompilerdevelopedby Welinq."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00513-y-pdf/metodo/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "In the following, we explain how multiple quantum gates can be distributed together, as a gate packet, using a single Tele Gate protocol (Sect.2.1)."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00513-y-pdf/metodo/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "Ourworkleveragesthenotionofgatepackets[16,17,23,24],which, combinedwithan efficient preprocessing circuit optimization method, yields a unique framework of distributed quantum compilation."
        }
      ],
      "temContribuicao": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s40507-026-00513-y-pdf/contribuicao/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "contribuicao",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "As a result, our framework provides a flexible and scalable solution suited for the demandsoffuturelarge-scalequantumcomputingarchitectures."
        }
