    {
      "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01146-2-pdf",
      "@type": [
        "ArtigoCientifico",
        "schema:ScholarlyArticle"
      ],
      "arquivo": "s41534-025-01146-2.pdf",
      "titulo": "npj | quantum information Article",
      "temObjetivo": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01146-2-pdf/objetivo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "We propose WT3 architecture in this work to lower the stringent entanglement generation requirements."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01146-2-pdf/objetivo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "Focusing on solid-state quantum hardware, we investigate the threshold and logical failure rate of a fully distributed surface code."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01146-2-pdf/objetivo/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "We consider both emission-based and scattering-based entanglement schemes between the modules to link the performance to the physical hardware and identify the regime for fault tolerance."
        }
      ],
      "temProblema": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01146-2-pdf/problema/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "However, identifying optimal architectures and entanglement generation protocols remains an open question."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01146-2-pdf/problema/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "While the RFL scheme requires optical circulators and a delay line to guide and manipulate the photons, which raises challenges in on-chip integrated photonics, the CAR scheme circumvents these problems."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01146-2-pdf/problema/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "For some entanglement schemes, thresholds nearing the thresholds of non-distributed implementations (~ 0.4%) appear feasible with future parameters minimizing the performance gap between modular and monolithic quantum processors."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01146-2-pdf/problema/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "Error-corrected1- 3 modular quantum computers4- 9 offer a promising route to overcome the noise and scalability challenges of large-scale fault-tolerant quantum computing."
        }
      ],
      "temMetodologia": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01146-2-pdf/metodo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "Set-2 has increased link coherence times by one order of magnitude, andfinally, we consider Set-3, which has coherence times of 10 Although our simulation model allows for distinct T1 and T2 times, for each communication and memory qubits, we considered Tdec 1;link ¼ Tdec 2; link and Tdec 1;idle ¼ Tdec 2; idle, where the subscripts 1, 2 denote the T1 and T2 decay times."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01146-2-pdf/metodo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "The FP sets are inspired by potential improvements in the experiments."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01146-2-pdf/metodo/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "The NTP sets are inspired by the same recent experiments as the RFL scheme parameters."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01146-2-pdf/metodo/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "Operation and coherence times We consider a broad set of coherence and operation time parameters as s h o w ni n F i g.9.T h e r e,Tdec link and Tdec idle describe the coherence times applicable to the CQs and memory qubits when entanglement generation is attempted and during idling, respectively."
        }
