      "temObjetivo": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01171-1-pdf/objetivo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "This work introduces a complete workflow from first principles for simulating corrosion processes."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01171-1-pdf/objetivo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "We present computational models for aqueous corrosion in magnesium and magnesium-aluminum alloy surf aces, which may be extendable to o t h e rm e t a l l i cs y s t e m s;a n df o rh i gh-temperature oxidation in niobium alloys, which are critical for extreme environments but highly susceptible to degradation."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01171-1-pdf/objetivo/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "Results We develop a hybrid classical-quantum workflow to investigate the corrosion mechanisms at the atomic scale in two classes of alloys, under aqueous and high-temperature environments."
        }
      ],
      "temProblema": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01171-1-pdf/problema/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "However, no single mathematical framework currently exists that can fully capture the complexity of the physical and chemical processes driving corrosion7,8."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01171-1-pdf/problema/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "Our models for magnesium corrosion are based on nudged elastic band modeling, while our niobium algorithm involves a coupledcluster approximation to map the problem to a classical Ising model."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01171-1-pdf/problema/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "We conduct a comprehensive resource assessment for quantum modeling of aqueous and high-temperature corrosion processes, marking the first application of the py LIQTR computational tool to a real-world materials science problem."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01171-1-pdf/problema/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "HER is further complicated by the highly-reactive, and short-lived corrosion intermediates formed during cathodic polarization, presenting a significant challenge in both computational and experiment al investigations of the reaction mechanism."
        }
      ],
      "temMetodologia": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01171-1-pdf/metodo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "This section describes the methodology for constructing classical-quantum hybrid workflows using the QBG framework and the methods used to estimate resources presented in the main paper."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01171-1-pdf/metodo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "The discretization error in this PW approach is asymptotically equivalent to Galerkin discretization s using other single-particle bases (including Gaussian orbitals)48.M o r e o v e r,t h efirst quantization framework offers a much more space-ef ficient (algorithmically) representation compared to the second quantization formalism."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01171-1-pdf/metodo/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "Quantum subroutines In this work, we employ the qubitized quantum phase estimation (QPE) algorithm, as described in ref. 46, to extract spectral information, specifically the ground state energies, for chemical systems of interest."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41534-025-01171-1-pdf/metodo/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "A major factor in the computational expense of using QPE for ground-state energy estimation lies in choosing the initial state for the algorithm."
        }
      ],
