    {
      "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41598-025-32572-z-pdf",
      "@type": [
        "ArtigoCientifico",
        "schema:ScholarlyArticle"
      ],
      "arquivo": "s41598-025-32572-z.pdf",
      "titulo": "Optimal compilation strategies",
      "temObjetivo": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41598-025-32572-z-pdf/objetivo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "To address this, we propose folding the linear layout into a two-dimensional grid while preserving the efficiency of the linear transformation."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41598-025-32572-z-pdf/objetivo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "This paper introduces optimal compilation strategies tailored to QFT circuits on the DPQA architecture, addressing these challenges for both linear and grid-like configurations."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41598-025-32572-z-pdf/objetivo/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "objetivo",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "Our contributions are threefold: • We propose a Linear Path strategy that achieves the theoretical lower bound in atom-movement count for one-dimensional linear DPQA processors. • We extend this approach to two-dimensional (2D) grid-like DPQA processors through a Zigzag Path strategy, which preserves gate parallelism while minimizing movement overhead. • We demonstrate that our methods outperform state-of-the-art DPQA compilers, including Enola 22 and Atomique23, achieving exponential improvements in movement efficiency and overall circuit fidelity."
        }
      ],
      "temProblema": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41598-025-32572-z-pdf/problema/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "However, the all-to-all interaction pattern of QFT poses significant challenges, especially in layouts with limited qubit connectivity."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41598-025-32572-z-pdf/problema/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "Despite these strengths, efficiently implementing quantum circuits like the Quantum Fourier Transform (QFT) remains a significant challenge due to atom-movement overheads and connectivity constraints."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41598-025-32572-z-pdf/problema/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "However, designing a general-purpose optimal compiler is fundamentally intractable, since optimal quantum circuit compilation is an NP-hard problem."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41598-025-32572-z-pdf/problema/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "problema",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "Hardware constraints such as limited qubit connectivity, short coherence times, and low gate fidelity necessitate optimizations tailored to specific platforms."
        }
      ],
      "temMetodologia": [
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41598-025-32572-z-pdf/metodo/1",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 1,
          "texto": "We implement Linear and Zigzag Paths in Python and employ Enola’s Code Gen framework 22 to generate gate execution and schedule movements."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41598-025-32572-z-pdf/metodo/2",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 2,
          "texto": "All experiments were conducted on a system running Ubuntu 22.04, equipped with a 40-core Intel Xeon Gold 5215 processor at 2.50 GHz and 512 GB of RAM."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41598-025-32572-z-pdf/metodo/3",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 3,
          "texto": "In this section, we evaluate the performance of our proposed methods (called Linear and Zigzag Paths, respectively) for transforming QFT circuits on the DPQA architecture."
        },
        {
          "@id": "http://example.org/trab2-ia/lucas-matheus/quantum-computing-nlp-analysis/artigo/s41598-025-32572-z-pdf/metodo/4",
          "@type": "TrechoExtraido",
          "categoria": "metodo",
          "ordem": 4,
          "texto": "Our evaluation aims to demonstrate the effectiveness of our methods in minimizing resource overheads while maintaining high-fidelity quantum operations."
        }
      ],
      "temContribuicao": [],
